---

<div class="mt-8 relative group">
  <!-- Corner decorations -->
  <div class="absolute -top-1 -left-1 w-3 h-3 border-t-2 border-l-2 border-emerald-400"></div>
  <div class="absolute -top-1 -right-1 w-3 h-3 border-t-2 border-r-2 border-cyan-400"></div>
  <div class="absolute -bottom-1 -left-1 w-3 h-3 border-b-2 border-l-2 border-cyan-400"></div>
  <div class="absolute -bottom-1 -right-1 w-3 h-3 border-b-2 border-r-2 border-emerald-400"></div>
  
  <!-- Animated gradient border -->
  <div class="p-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 via-cyan-500 to-blue-500 rounded-lg animate-gradient-shift">
    <!-- Animated glow effect -->
    <div class="absolute -inset-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 via-cyan-500 to-blue-500 rounded-lg blur opacity-20 group-hover:opacity-40 transition duration-1000 -z-10"></div>
    
    <!-- Grid pattern overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-5 pointer-events-none" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(5, 150, 105, 0.1) 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.1) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 20px 20px;"></div>
    
    <!-- Main content container -->
    <div class="relative bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <!-- Title with scan line effect -->
      <div class="relative mb-3">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2 text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 animate-pulse" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
          <span class="font-mono tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-transparent dark:bg-clip-text dark:bg-gradient-to-r dark:from-emerald-400 dark:to-cyan-400">Security Analysis: How This Message System Works</span>
        </h3>
        <!-- Underline with animation -->
        <div class="h-[1px] bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-600 dark:from-emerald-400 via-cyan-600 dark:via-cyan-400 to-transparent mt-1 animate-expand"></div>
      </div>
  
  <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
    <div class="group/item">
      <p class="border-l-2 border-green-500 pl-3 transition-all hover:border-l-4 hover:pl-4 hover:bg-green-500/5 py-1.5 -ml-0.5 rounded-r">
        <span class="font-semibold text-green-500 font-mono">[✓]</span> 
        <span class="font-medium text-green-500">Static Website Protection:</span> 
        <span class="text-base-content/80">This website is served by GitHub Pages over HTTPS. The website files themselves are protected in transit, but GitHub Pages only serves static content.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="group/item">
      <p class="border-l-2 border-amber-500 pl-3 transition-all hover:border-l-4 hover:pl-4 hover:bg-amber-500/5 py-1.5 -ml-0.5 rounded-r">
        <span class="font-semibold text-amber-500 font-mono">[!]</span> 
        <span class="font-medium text-amber-500">Message Transmission:</span>
        <span class="text-base-content/80">Your messages are sent directly from your browser to n8n automation service over HTTPS (encrypted in transit) but are accessible in unencrypted form within the n8n service itself.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="group/item">
      <p class="border-l-2 border-red-500 pl-3 transition-all hover:border-l-4 hover:pl-4 hover:bg-red-500/5 py-1.5 -ml-0.5 rounded-r">
        <span class="font-semibold text-red-500 font-mono">[×]</span> 
        <span class="font-medium text-red-500">Third-Party Processing:</span>
        <span class="text-base-content/80">After processing, messages are sent to Telegram through their API. Both n8n and Telegram servers can technically access the message content.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Divider with scanning effect -->
  <div class="mt-4 pt-3 relative">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500/20 via-cyan-500/20 to-blue-500/20"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-cyan-400 to-transparent animate-scan"></div>
    
    <p class="text-sm text-base-content/80 mb-3">
      This system shows why cryptography matters: even with HTTPS protection, your messages are readable by intermediaries (n8n, Telegram). 
      The solution? <strong class="text-emerald-400">Encrypt messages before sending them.</strong> Try it yourself with <code class="bg-black/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-400 text-[11px] font-mono border border-cyan-500/20 hover:border-cyan-500/40 transition-colors">/encrypt &lt;your message&gt;</code> in the terminal above.
    </p>
    
    <!-- Research focus with animated border -->
    <div class="mt-3 p-3 relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500/5 to-cyan-500/5 border border-emerald-400/30 rounded group/research hover:border-emerald-400/60 transition-all">
      <!-- Animated corner accent -->
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-400/10 to-transparent rounded-bl-full group-hover/research:w-20 group-hover/research:h-20 transition-all duration-500"></div>
      
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-base-content/90 leading-relaxed relative">
        <span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono text-xs mr-1">//</span>
        My research focuses on <span class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold">building the mathematical foundations</span> that make secure encryption possible: 
        designing and analyzing <span class="text-cyan-400 font-medium">block ciphers</span>, <span class="text-cyan-400 font-medium">hash functions</span>, and <span class="text-cyan-400 font-medium">cryptographic primitives</span>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  @keyframes gradient-shift {
    0%, 100% {
      background-position: 0% 50%;
    }
    50% {
      background-position: 100% 50%;
    }
  }
  
  @keyframes scan {
    0% {
      transform: translateX(-100%);
    }
    100% {
      transform: translateX(200%);
    }
  }
  
  @keyframes expand {
    0% {
      width: 0%;
    }
    100% {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
  
  .animate-gradient-shift {
    background-size: 200% 200%;
    animation: gradient-shift 3s ease infinite;
  }
  
  .animate-scan {
    animation: scan 3s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  
  .animate-expand {
    animation: expand 1s ease-out forwards;
  }
</style>
